  "id": "MAL-2026-5412",
  "summary": "Malicious code in @klapp-kyc/routes (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (ad94c92fd5b9921bc74eebca1ec5a25c4547ca62c54d9026850535d2f4c39849)\n@klapp-kyc/routes@99.0.1 declares `preinstall: node index.js` in package.json, causing index.js to execute automatically on `npm install`. The script collects host identity fields (os.hostname(), os.userInfo().username, __dirname, process.cwd(), package name) and exfiltrates them through two channels: (1) hex-encoded as DNS labels to a subdomain of `d8jbmnsqcfu78dfs8vdg34ohqhirb4pbg.oast.live` via dns.resolve, and (2) HTTP POSTed as JSON to the bare IP `172.201.213.59:9090/c`. The package's `description` field is \"security research\" and its version (99.0.1) is the canonical high-semver shape used to outrank a legitimate internal `@klapp-kyc` package in dependency-confusion attacks. The combination of inflated version, scope targeting, OAST callback, and bare-IP POST is an unambiguous supply-chain reconnaissance/exfiltration beacon.\n",
